description: A textual description of the entity. This value
should include the full name and version
identification of the system's hardware type
software operating-system, and networking
software. It is mandatory that this only contain
printable ASCII characters.
variables.name: RFC1213-MIB::sysDescr

description: The physical location of this node (e.g.
`telephone closet, 3rd floor').
variables.name: RFC1213-MIB::sysLocation

description: The alarm priority level.
In Mirador, priority 1 corresponds to a critical alarm.
priority 2 corresponds to a major alarm.
priority 3 corresponds to a minor alarm.
priority 4 corresponds to an informational alarm.
variables.name: MULTITEL-DOME-MIB::domeAlarmPriority

description: A unique identifier for an alarm condition. A particular alarm
always gets the same ID each time it goes ON as long as the
application configuration is not changed.
variables.name: MULTITEL-DOME-MIB::domeAlarmID

description: The alarm configured mnemonic.
variables.name: MULTITEL-DOME-MIB::domeAlarmMnemonic

description: The alarm configured name.
variables.name: MULTITEL-DOME-MIB::domeAlarmName

description: Occurrence counter. Number of time the alarm turned ON.
variables.name: MULTITEL-DOME-MIB::domeAlarmOcc

description: This object is use to bind some text to the trap.
The content of the text is configurable.
variables.name: MULTITEL-DOME-MIB::domeTrapString

description: System date and time.
variables.name: MULTITEL-GENERIC-MIB::multitelSystemDateTime
